==English==

===Etymology 1===
Late {{inh|en|enm|-}}, from [[w:British Latin|British]] {{der|en|VL.|peta}}, probably ultimately from a {{der|en|cel|-}} language such as an unattested {{der|en|xpi|-}} or {{der|en|cel-bry|-}} source, in turn possibly from {{der|en|cel-bry-pro|*peθ||portion, segment, piece}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|en|/piːt/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-peat.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|iːt|s=1}}
* {{homophones|en|Pete}}

====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}

# Soil formed of dead but not fully [[decay|decayed]] [[plant]]s found in [[bog]] areas, often burned as fuel. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}

